<unit id="a3c954d8-c424-480a-af5d-dc2dd5fada80">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 2</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: # </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Ask OpenRouter</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="258f1957-d6a1-444d-8941-65e28cc607a0">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 4</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Author(s) : Abdel.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="90e23775-2ca4-4214-b802-d8484a01bc0f">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 6</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>This NVDA add-on allows you to interact with Artificial Intelligence models provided by the OpenRouter platform directly from your screen reader.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="6fbcd087-293e-4165-8ae8-03aa7c6928ac">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 8</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>The add-on supports both:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="47a3785a-05fb-4670-9aeb-ad0521bec60b">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 9</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Automatic random selection of free models</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="c63b62b2-2b66-4ce8-a3cc-d1b3720f3ae0">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 10</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Manual selection of any available model (including paid ones)</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="5b41264b-033f-4404-bdce-19e158a280e9">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 12</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Key Features</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="b9bf658b-4659-43ce-b035-23f0a0afca90">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 14</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Quick Access: Open the chat interface anytime with a global shortcut.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="0df086c3-0a9c-4e2c-804a-b54fe75ca9f7">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 15</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Conversation Management: Start a fresh conversation or continue your previous exchange.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="8e412176-b650-46c7-8628-24ed6e5ceb5f">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 16</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Smart Free Model Rotation: Automatically selects a random free model to optimize daily usage quotas.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="aad76cba-9d84-4687-bc92-fe6bac9b2926">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 17</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Manual Model Selection: Choose a specific model (including paid models) from the settings panel.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="5acc5bbf-9fff-4ef9-a404-e96d05b9eb2e">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 18</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Accessible Results: View responses in a clear, easy-to-navigate window with optional full history display.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="73d17a7c-86af-4d1f-b0d9-7ded7e522ddb">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 20</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Configuration: Obtaining and Installing Your API Key</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="ed60b698-1ba0-4793-b646-93a7490cf735">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 22</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>To use this add-on, you must have an API key from OpenRouter.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="a682bc2d-7306-4d59-8929-e9e1945fd519">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 24</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Even when using free models, the key is required to identify your requests.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="8714d16e-2f56-40d9-8942-f9b190909352">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 26</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ### </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>1. How to get an API key</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="6ff1315a-ee1c-4d9f-87d9-edb6d0a57195">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 28</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: 1. </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Go to [OpenRouter.ai](https://openrouter.ai/).</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="8903f3d3-80a7-438c-a8e5-62f8c47cd9b2">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 29</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: 2. </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Create an account by clicking "Sign up" (you can sign in with a GitHub, Google or MetaMask account, or your email address).</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="630e66b2-b7f0-4777-9560-c00cb8ca2e21">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 30</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: 3. </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Once logged in, navigate to the "Keys" section in your dashboard, or go directly to: https://openrouter.ai/keys</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="c2a266e9-6894-4ca9-84bd-dd7cf26abd33">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 31</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: 4. </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Click the "Create Key" button.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="d5861f44-7aa2-48ad-a3aa-04d2a399157a">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 32</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: 5. </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Give your key a name (for example: "My OpenRouter API key") and click "Create".</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="5f30e3d7-20be-4778-a552-b36d1c3760cf">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 33</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: 6. </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Important: Your key will be displayed only once. Copy it immediately and store it in a secure place.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="409c233d-dd3a-4df0-8793-bf703acf6f14">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 35</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ### </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>2. Setting up the key in NVDA</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="64adbe62-995b-4943-8a72-53b4baa2f24e">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 37</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: 1. </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Open the NVDA menu (NVDA + N).</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="6c1bcd63-1a26-450e-822c-2a3ea1d3b521">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 38</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: 2. </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Navigate to Preferences, then Settings.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="5f88b52b-bea3-4b76-876f-0cb6fa57afdb">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 39</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: 3. </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>In the categories list, select "Ask OpenRouter".</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="43f6902a-cb46-41bf-9d90-495c45e0047e">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 40</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: 4. </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Paste your API key into the "OpenRouter API Key" field.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="1674420f-ec70-43ce-a34a-3a838ec5d512">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 41</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: 5. </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Press OK to save.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="e07eec86-0f2a-420e-b60a-e623476865c1">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 43</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: #### </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Show API Key</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="a9f02e60-74b9-4b20-bfea-da309c084e95">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 45</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>In the NVDA settings panel, just after the "OpenRouter API Key" field, there is a checkbox labeled:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="c0f8466a-003b-4497-9b2f-1cb19a48882c">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 47</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>"Show API key"</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="f3ff0d17-6d01-42ab-ad28-f55507a2c2d0">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 49</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>If checked, the characters of the API key become visible.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="d20b9570-27e3-413e-9b69-990be3e116fe">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 50</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>By default, they are hidden for security reasons.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="eac2b838-95de-4b2f-ba4e-fc654e283f3f">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 52</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Model Selection Settings</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="bdafc0c2-1987-4c85-890e-e71d6d24855a">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 54</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>In the Ask OpenRouter settings category, you will find a new option:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="84d08760-8a1f-4585-b7f5-50a2623437a8">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 56</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ### </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>"Use all models, including paid ones"</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="2fe8f318-049e-48bb-a6c4-0c6f25c935e3">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 58</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>This option controls how models are selected.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="7cdefbab-d87b-40f2-b0da-f164a1b4117d">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 60</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ### </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>When the option is UNCHECKED (default behavior)</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="d33dc03b-f741-4770-92eb-11f59368678c">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 62</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>The add-on automatically selects a random free model for each new conversation.</source>
</segment>
